law.text:
In this subtitle, "displaced homemaker" means an individual who:
is at least 35 years old;
has worked for the individual's family in the family home;
is not gainfully employed;
has had, or would have, difficulty in securing employment; and
has depended on:
the income of a family member and has lost that income as the result of separation, divorce, or the death or disability of that family member; or
government assistance as the parent of a dependent child and is no longer eligible for that assistance.
